# TRIBE Specification Overhaul — Walkthrough

## Summary
Completely rewrote `tribe_specification.md` to address all 25+ architectural issues raised. The document grew from **387 lines → 580+ lines** with 5 new database collections, 3 new workflow sections, a full tournament architecture, and a premium theme redesign.

---

## Changes by Category

### 🗄️ Schema Extraction (Issues #1, #2, #3)
| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| `chatHistory` unbounded array in Lobby | Extracted to **Messages** collection with `{ lobbyId, createdAt }` index |
| `availableTimeSlots` unbounded array in Venue | Extracted to **TimeSlots** collection with `{ venueId, pitchName, startTime, status }` index |
| `roster`/`waitlist` embedded in Lobby | Extracted to **JoinRequests** collection. Lobby now only has lean `confirmedPlayerIds` array (bounded by match size) |

### ⚡ Concurrency & Race Conditions (Issue #5)
- All slot modifications use `findOneAndUpdate` with `{ openSlots: { $gt: 0 } }` atomic guard
- Documented in Section 2.4, 4.1, and 4.5
- `openSlots` can be validated against `totalSlots - confirmedPlayerIds.length` for drift detection

### 🕐 Lobby Lifecycle (Issue #6)
- Added `expiresAt` field to Lobby schema (computed as `dateTime + 2 hours`)
- New **Section 4.6** documents BullMQ recurring job for auto-transitioning expired lobbies
- Added `COMPLETED` and `EXPIRED` to status enum

### 👤 User Model (Issues #10, #18)
- `role: "String"` → `roles: ["String"]` array. A venue owner can also play matches
- Added `notificationPreferences` object with granular per-channel, per-type toggles
- Added `avatarUrl` for S3/Cloudinary profile photos
- Added `location` with 2dsphere index for Ringer proximity queries

### 💰 Revenue Cleanup (Issue #4)
- Removed all "revenue generation" references from analytics/admin dashboard
- `hourlyRate` stays but explicitly labeled "informational only, display purposes"
- Added clear statement: "All actual payments are handled entirely offline"

### 🔧 Infrastructure (Issues #7, #9)
- **Socket.io scaling:** Documented `@socket.io/redis-adapter` with Redis pub/sub, sticky sessions via NGINX `ip_hash`
- **Waitlist timers:** Documented BullMQ for persistent delayed jobs. No `setTimeout` used anywhere
- Added BullMQ to tech stack (Section 2.1)

### ✅ Validation (Issues #11, #15, #28, #29)
- **Sport validation:** Added `sportConfig` map with actual code example in Section 9
- **Duplicate prevention:** Unique compound index `{ lobbyId, userId }` on JoinRequests
- **Rate limiting:** Concrete limits defined (10/min auth, 5/min joins, 3/hr lobby creation, etc.)
- **Timezone:** All dates stored UTC. Explicit `timezone` field on lobbies, time slots, challenges, tournaments

### 🔄 Missing Workflows (Issues #16, #17)
- **New Section 4.7:** Cancellation & Dropout — `APPROVED → DROPPED_OUT` transition, waitlist cascade, ringer trigger
- **New Section 4.8:** Venue Booking Cancellation — 24-hour restriction, slot status revert, venue notification
- Added `PATCH /request/:id/dropout`, `PATCH /request/:id/cancel`, `DELETE /venues/:id/bookings/:slotId`

### 🏆 Tournament System (Issue #12)
- **New Section 10:** Full tournament architecture
- Supports 4 formats: Single Elimination, Double Elimination, Round Robin, Group Stage + Knockout
- Schema-less `bracket` field for format flexibility
- Tournament matches reuse existing Lobby infrastructure
- Dedicated pages: `/tournaments` and `/tournament/:id`
- API: `GET/POST /tournaments`, `POST /:id/register`, `PATCH /:id/bracket`

### ⚔️ Squad vs. Squad (Issue #13)
- **New Section 4.3:** Complete challenge workflow
- New **Challenges** collection and API (`/api/challenges`)
- Challenge → Accept → Auto-creates Lobby with both squad rosters pre-populated
- Public browsing with optional private challenges
- Auto-expiry via BullMQ/TTL

### 🔍 Squad Discovery (Issue #19)
- Added `GET /api/squads` with sport/location filters
- New **Squad Discovery** page at `/squads`
- Squad collection gets `location` with 2dsphere index and `sport` field

### 🏟️ Venue Flexibility (User request)
- `pitches.sport: "String"` → `pitches.sports: ["String"]` — each pitch declares which sports it supports
- Added detailed note explaining multi-sport pitches (e.g., Multi-Court → `["Basketball", "Volleyball"]`)
- Lobby creation filters venue pitches by selected sport
- Time slots managed per-pitch independently

### 📷 File Storage (Issue #27)
- Added AWS S3/Cloudinary to tech stack
- `avatarUrl` on User, `logoUrl` on Squad, `photos` array on Venue
- Presigned URLs for secure client uploads, Sharp.js for thumbnails

### 🎨 Theme Overhaul
Replaced the neon/dark theme with **"Warm Precision"** — a Linear/Stripe/Vercel-inspired design system:
- Warm off-whites (`#FAF9F7`) and atmospheric charcoal (`#1A1A1A`) — never pure black/white
- **Burnt Coral** (`#E8614D`) accent used sparingly for CTAs
- **Teal** (`#2A9D8F`) for success states
- **Outfit** + **Inter** + **JetBrains Mono** typography system
- Bento-box cards with thin borders and subtle shadows
- Glassmorphism reserved for modals only
- Skeleton loading screens instead of spinners
- First-class dark mode with smooth crossfade transitions

### 🚫 Removed
- `skillLevel` / `skillsRequired` — removed from lobby schema, user profile, feed filters, and lobby creation
- All "revenue generation" language from analytics and admin dashboard
- Neon green / electric blue color references

### ➕ Added (Beyond Issues)
- **Section 11:** Future Considerations (i18n, payments, mobile app, AI recommendations)
- `location` field + 2dsphere index on User schema for Ringer geoproximity
- Challenge socket events (`challenge_posted`, `challenge_accepted`)
- `player_dropped` and `booking_cancelled` socket events
- Lobby scope clarification paragraph in schema section
